7.4.25  2:11 pm   The way I like to think of genres is that, instead of being strict categories that artists or songs have to fit in, they're just labels you can put on a song that describe a specific aspect of the song, be it when it was made, the instrumentation used, the way it's produced, the lyrical content, etc. and since most songs are quite multifaceted, most songs can have several genres attributed to them, and this combination of genres, together, constitutes an (albeit rough and imperfect) description of the song, that gives you a (rough and imperfect) idea of what to expect from that song.
